  Function:  onoff
      Desc:  echo 1 if 'on', 0 if 'off'
          : 
  Synopsis:  onoff on|1 || off|0 [defaultval]
          :  for ambiguous value, returns defaultval if defined, otherwise 0.
          : 
   Example:  result=$(onoff off 1)
          : 
       Url: file:///usr/share/e.bash/e.bash
